name: Hell Is Other People
description:
The stoics believed that people are our proper occupation. That investing in the people around you is the work that is most worth doing in this life. Jean-Paul Sartre said in his play No Exit, that "Hell is other people." I have felt both of these concepts, in varying shades and applications, very deeply these past two years. Maybe you have too.
